        <tr>
          <td>
            <p><a id="P018353"></a>Episodes of <strong>ventricular</strong> <strong>asystole</strong>
              may complicate complete heart block or Mobitz type II
              second-degree AV block, or occur in patients with sinoatrial
              disease (see Fig. 18.50). This may cause recurrent <strong>syncope</strong>
              or 'Stokes-Adams' attacks.</p>
          </td>
